-- EU Carbon Little Changed as Fortum's Third-Quarter Emissions Decline 17%
-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 2010-10-21T07:59:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/eu-carbon-little-changed-as-fortum-s-third-quarter-emissions-decline-17-.html
European Union carbon-dioxide
allowances were little changed as  Fortum Oyj , Finland’s biggest
utility, said its emissions in the bloc’s program fell 17
percent in the third quarter.  The utility group said emissions trading system output
declined to 1 million metric tons from 1.2 million tons a year
earlier, Espoo, Finland-based Fortum said today in a statement
distributed by the Helsinki Stock Exchange newswire.  EU permits for December fell 1 cent, or 0.1 percent, to
15.14 euros ($21.14) a metric ton as of 8:43 a.m. on London’s
European Climate Exchange. They’ve dropped 2 percent this week.
German power for settlement next year declined 0.2 percent to
48.05 euros a megawatt-hour, according to broker data compiled
by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Mathew Carr  in London at 
